### Overview
~~Provide basic functionality that replicates junit4's `@ClassRule` lifecycle by implementing an [`Extension`](http://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/user-guide/#extensions) for [`BeforeAllCallback`](http://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/api/org/junit/jupiter/api/extension/BeforeAllCallback.html) and [`AfterAllCallback`](http://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/api/org/junit/jupiter/api/extension/AfterAllCallback.html) dubbed `DockerComposeExtension` that uses reflection on the junit5 class to manipulate docker compose / machine state.  Basic expected usage is outlined below.~~

### Usage
```java

import org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;
import com.palantir.docker.compose.DockerComposeExtension;

@ExtendWith(DockerComposeExtension.class)
class Junit5Tests {

     // The DockerComposeExtension will reflect on static fields for Junit5Tests
     // and control state as class container starts (before all tests) and when class container stops (after all tests)
     static final DockerComposeRule DOCKER_COMPOSE = DockerComposeRule.builder()
                                   // All the usual stuff
                                   .build();

     @Test
     void testThing() {
          // Standard test
     }

     @ParameterizedTest
     void testParameterized(String input) {
           // Parameterized test bound to the test class container lifecycle
     }

     @TestFactory
     Stream<DynamicTest> testFactory() {
          // Also should support @TestFactory since it's also bound to the parent class container lifecycle
     }

}
```

